reviewText:
Justin (Taran Killam) gets publicly dumped and humiliated by his now ex-girlfriend Sarah (Aimee-Lynn Chadwick). His workmates help him out with an Internet date called "Casual Encounters." He works for Cal Telcom, pronounce Telecom. Justin has the proverbial female office mate (Brooklyn Decker) that has an interest in him....Internet dates show up in real life etc. formula, barf writing.

We know how this turns out 5 minutes into the film. The predictability factor was extremely high, Justin's sad sack character not likeable. Not worthy of a date night film.

Guide: F-word, sex, nudity.
Cute feel good movie , we would watch it again
Was a decent movie but not one to watch over again
A great Sat. nite 'date' flick.  Heart warning.
Nothing crazy, cute movie to watch with my girlfriend. We both enjoyed it.

Funny, OK, movie to watch with your spouse! I wouldn't have paid money to see it in the theater though.

CPS
Absolutely one of the worst movies I've ever seen. Same old breakup story with boy meets new girl, they fall in love, out of love and then back into love... Blah, waste of time.
Exactly what I thought would be
